node.text:
Meet Joswin, professional cinematographer and founder of Bike LA. When the pandemic hit and his work slowed down, Joswin turned his passion for bike-riding into his muse. His camera of choice? The Google Pixel. By documenting his rides and popular Los Angeles landmarks, he built a thriving community that feels like family.

Watch Joswin’s True Pixel story and see how his Pixel helped him grow Bike LA.

node.title: Leader of the Pack - Joswin True Pixel Story

node.text: In celebration of #Juneteenth, Local Guide @theAprilHamm is visiting historic places in New Orleans — like Congo Square and the Free People of Color Museum — and adding information about them to the map to make history more accessible. Her contributions show that being a Local Guide on @googlemaps is more than leaving reviews — it’s a way to share and commemorate history.

node.title: Preserving Black History on Google Maps
